## tool-sysprompt: sysprompt tool definitions

These tools are also available through the unified sysprompt_cfg resource tool.

### sysprompt_list(model: str) -> str
List all .system_prompt* files in the model's system prompt folder.
Use model="self" to refer to the current model.

### sysprompt_read(model: str, file: str = "") -> str
Read the assembled system prompt for a model.
Omit file to get the full assembled prompt. Specify a section name (e.g. "behavior") to read one file.
Use model="self" for the current model.

### sysprompt_write(model: str, file: str, data: str) -> str
Overwrite or create a system prompt section file for a model.
Use model="self" for the current model.
file: section name ("behavior") or full filename (".system_prompt_behavior").
WARNING: Replaces the entire file.

### sysprompt_delete(model: str, file: str = "") -> str
Delete a specific system prompt file, or the entire folder if file is omitted.
Omitting file deletes the entire directory and sets system_prompt_folder="none".
Use model="self" for the current model.

### sysprompt_copy_dir(model: str, new_dir: str) -> str
Copy a model's system prompt folder to a new directory under system_prompt/.
Use model="self" for the current model.

### sysprompt_set_dir(model: str, new_dir: str) -> str
Assign a model's system_prompt_folder to an existing directory under system_prompt/.
Use new_dir="none" to clear the folder. Persists to llm-models.json.
